Manchester United midfielder, Paul Pogba’s possible next club has been revealed. According to L’Equipe, Pogba, whose contract with Man United will expire at the end of the season, is likely to join Paris Saint-Germain this year. The 28-year-old is yet to sign a new contract with Man United. The France international has drawn the interest of PSG, Juventus and Real Madrid in the past. Pogba is free this month to speak to foreign clubs over a free summer transfer. Meanwhile, Juventus are plotting a move for Chelsea star, Ruben Loftus-Cheek, Sky Sports Italy reports. Juventus have identified Loftus-Cheek as a possible replacement for Arthur Melo, who has been linked with a move away from the Old Lady to Arsenal this January transfer window. The Serie A giants want to sign the England midfielder on a permanent deal. The report added that Juve also have two alternatives, Lyon’s Bruno Guimaraes and Lille’s Renato Sanches should they fail to sign Loftus-Cheek. EPL: Varane to double Real Madrid wage at Man Utd